<SCHEMA-FIELD-GUIDANCE>
- module: Derive from folder/file grouping; if unclear use `"__UNSET__"`.
- constants: Domain constants only; omit infra/env (URLs, keys). Provide exact literal snippet.
- types: Descriptive only. List field names or enum variants exactly as seen. If absent use `"__UNSET__"`. No inference.
  - fields: Each raw field identifier appearing in business logic context (string list, not objects).
  - variants: Enum variant identifiers and/or explicit numeric/string discriminants if present.
  - serialization_hints: Decorators / converters (e.g. boolean/number/enums) that influence domain semantics.
- functions: Business logic only.
  - rules: One domain rule per array item; do not merge.
  - decision_points: Each conditional with exact condition and explicit outcome.
  - mappings: Lookup or conversion operations; keep source/target literal.
  - transformations: Object construction, field normalization, space removal, timestamp parsing.
  - filters: Predicates causing exclusion or early return.
  - calculations: Deterministic numeric/time math.
  - effectful_calls: Direct external calls inside the function used for immediate logic.
  - constants_used: Names of constants referenced literally.
EMPTY COLLECTIONS: Use `[]`. Missing scalars: `"__UNSET__"`.
